The Federal Road Safety Corps yesterday confirmed seven people killed in a crash at Osi Bridge on the Old Ilorin-Jebba-Mokwa Road in Ilorin East Local Government Area of Kwara State. The victims included three males and four females; while the injured were 34 adult females and 24 adult males. Among the injured were 12 children. FRSC Sector Commander Uchechukwu Wihioka attributed the crash, involving Toyota Dyna with registration number FA 655 NAS and Toyota Hiace with registration number LSD 919 SR, to wrong overtaking. 3 killed, 4 injured in Awawa auto crash 3-year-old injured in Yangoji  auto crash 5 killed, 2 injured in Adabo auto crash